  <h1>Lyve — Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="meta">Operated by TevDed (Teddy) · Contact: <a href="mailto:tevded@gmail.com">tevded@gmail.com</a><br />
  Effective date: June 23, 2026</p>

  <p>Lyve is a browser extension that adds a time-synced chat experience to YouTube videos.
  This policy explains what data Lyve collects, how it is used, and your choices. By creating
  an account or posting messages in Lyve, you agree to this policy.</p>

  <h2>1. Who operates Lyve</h2>
  <p>Lyve is developed and published by <strong>TevDed</strong>. For any privacy questions or
  data requests, contact <a href="mailto:tevded@gmail.com">tevded@gmail.com</a>.</p>

  <h2>2. Data we collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Email address</strong> — used to create and sign in to your Lyve account.</li>
    <li><strong>Password</strong> — entered to authenticate. It is transmitted directly to Google
      Firebase Authentication and is <em>not</em> stored or readable by the extension.</li>
    <li><strong>Display name / username</strong> — shown next to your messages.</li>
    <li><strong>Chat messages</strong> — the text you post, along with the YouTube
      <strong>video ID</strong> and the video timestamp the message is anchored to.</li>
    <li><strong>Authentication tokens</strong> — issued by Firebase and stored locally on your
      device (via <code>chrome.storage.local</code>) to keep you signed in.</li>
    <li><strong>Local preferences</strong> — chat settings (e.g. display name, colors, layout
      options) stored locally on your device.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Lyve does <strong>not</strong> collect your browsing history, location, financial information,
  health information, or the content of web pages other than the YouTube video ID needed to
  attach your chat messages to a video.</p>

  <h2>3. How we use data</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To authenticate your account and keep you signed in.</li>
    <li>To store chat messages and display them to other users watching the same video.</li>
    <li>To manage access during the private beta (an approved-users allowlist).</li>
    <li>To remember your local chat preferences.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Where data is stored and processed</h2>
  <p>Account and message data are stored using <strong>Google Firebase</strong> (Firebase
  Authentication and Cloud Firestore), running on Google Cloud infrastructure. Authentication
  tokens and preferences are stored locally in your browser. All network communication uses HTTPS.</p>

  <h2>5. Sharing and disclosure</h2>
  <p>We do <strong>not</strong> sell your data, and we do not share it with third parties for
  advertising. Data is processed only by Google Firebase as our hosting and authentication
  provider. Chat messages and your display name are visible to other Lyve users viewing the
  same video, which is the core function of the product. We do not use or transfer your data
  for any purpose unrelated to Lyve, and we do not use it to determine creditworthiness or for
  lending purposes.</p>

  <h2>6. Data retention and deletion</h2>
  <p>Your account and messages are retained until you request deletion. To delete your account
  and associated data, email <a href="mailto:tevded@gmail.com">tevded@gmail.com</a> and we will
  remove your account and messages from our systems.</p>

  <h2>7. Children</h2>
  <p>Lyve is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal
  information from them. If you believe a child has provided us personal information, contact
  <a href="mailto:tevded@gmail.com">tevded@gmail.com</a> and we will delete it.</p>

  <h2>8. Security</h2>
  <p>We rely on Google Firebase's security infrastructure, transmit all data over HTTPS, and
  store authentication tokens locally on your device. No method of transmission or storage is
  100% secure, but we take reasonable measures to protect your information.</p>

  <h2>9. Relationship to YouTube</h2>
  <p>Lyve is an independent third-party extension. It is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or
  sponsored by YouTube or Google LLC.</p>

  <h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be reflected by updating
  the effective date above.</p>

